    (iii)
    <br>
    ─ 9 < 3x divide both sides by 3
    <br>
    <sup>−9</sup>&frasl;<sub>3</sub> < <sup>3x</sup>&frasl;<sub>3</sub>
    <br>
    −3 < x <=> x > −3
    <br>
    <strong>x > −3 </strong>
    </div>
    <div class="col">
    (iv)
    <br>
    18  ≥ ─3 ─3x
    <br>
    18 + 3 ≥ − 3x
    <br>
    21 ≥ − 3x divide both sides by −3
    <br>
    <sup>21</sup>&frasl;<sub>-3</sub> ≥ <sup>−3x</sup>&frasl;<sub>─3</sub>; <strong>When dividing by negative (─), the inequality sign will change</strong>
    <br>
    ─ 7 ≤ x  <=>  x ≥ ─ 7
    <br>
    <strong>x  ≥  ─ 7</strong>
    </div>
  </div>
  </div>
<br>
