  <strong>Example 1</strong>
  <br>
  A rectangle has a length of 6metres and breadth of y metres. Find the range of y if the perimeter of the rectangle is not greater than 40metres and not less than 16metres.
  <br>
  <strong>Solution</strong>
  <br>
  <div class="container">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col border-right border-danger">
    <strong>First condition;</strong> perimeter not greater than 40m means   ≤ 40m
    <br>
    Perimeter = 2length x 2breadth
    <br>
    2(6) + 2y  ≤ 40
    <br>
    12 + 2y  ≤ 40
    <br>
    2y  ≤ 40 – 12
    <br> 
    2y  ≤ 28 divide both sides 2
    <br>
    <sup>2y</sup>&frasl;<sub>2</sub> ≤ <sup>28</sup>&frasl;<sub>2</sub>
    <br>
    <strong>y  ≤ 14</strong>
    </div>
    <div class="col">
    <strong> Second condition; </strong>perimeter not less than ≥ 16m
    <br>
     2(6) + 2y ≥ 16
     <br>
     12 + 2y ≥ 16
     <br> 
     2y ≥ 16 – 12
     <br> 
     2y ≥ 4 divide both sides by 2
     <br>
     <sup>2y</sup>&frasl;<sub>2</sub> ≥ <sup>4</sup>&frasl;<sub>2</sub>
     <br>
     <strong>y ≥ 2</strong>
     <br>
     The values of y are between <strong>2 to 14</strong> i.e. 2 ≤ y ≤ 14
     </div>
  </div>
